Here's the full program and output:

**`Program.cs`**
```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Alice", 30);

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase,
    WriteIndented = true
};

string json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options);
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string name, int age);
```

**Output:**
```json
{
  "Name": "Alice",
  "Age": 30
}
```

`JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase` is new in .NET 11 — it joins the existing built-in policies (`CamelCase`, `SnakeCaseLower`, `SnakeCaseUpper`, `KebabCaseLower`, `KebabCaseUpper`). It converts the lowercase record parameter names (`name`, `age`) to PascalCase (`Name`, `Age`) automatically.
